## **Security Audit Report: pi-minimal-subagent**

**Severity Summary:** 6 findings | 3 High | 2 Medium | 1 Low

---

### **1. PATH TRAVERSAL VIA AGENT NAME** [HIGH]
**File:** `src/agents/manager.ts:36, :53, :84`

```typescript
const filePath = path.join(projectAgentsDir(cwd), `${input.name.trim()}.md`);
```

**Risk:** Agent names pass through `NAME_PATTERN` regex check but can still contain `../` sequences. The regex allows spaces, dots, and hyphens—an attacker could register an agent named `"../../etc/passwd"` and traverse directories.

**Proof of Concept:**
```typescript
const agent = { name: "test../../../sensitive", description: "x", model: "gpt-4" };
// Resolves to: cwd/.pi/agents/test../../../sensitive.md
// → Actual path: cwd/sensitive.md (file written outside intended dir)
```

**Fix:**
```typescript
const NAME_PATTERN = /^[a-z0-9]([a-z0-9_-]{0,126})?$/i;  // No dots, no spaces
// Enforce absolute path containment:
const filePath = path.join(projectAgentsDir(cwd), `${input.name.trim()}.md`);
const realPath = path.resolve(filePath);
const baseDir = path.resolve(projectAgentsDir(cwd));
if (!realPath.startsWith(baseDir + path.sep)) {
  throw new Error("Agent name escapes project directory");
}
```

---

### **2. COMMAND INJECTION VIA ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES** [HIGH]
**File:** `src/settings/settings-parsers.ts:1–22` & `src/execution/runner.ts:buildChildEnv()`

```typescript
export function parseEnvironment(value: unknown): Record<string, string> | undefined {
  const environment: Record<string, string> = {};
  for (const [rawKey, rawValue] of Object.entries(value as Record<string, unknown>)) {
    const key = rawKey.trim();
    if (!key || key.includes("=") || key.includes("\0") || 
        typeof rawValue !== "string" || rawValue.includes("\0")) continue;
    environment[key] = rawValue;  // ← No escaping; raw value passed to spawn()
  }
  return environment;
}
```

**Risk:** Environment variables are passed directly to child processes via `spawn()`. A malicious override like `PATH="/tmp/evil;/usr/bin"` or `LD_PRELOAD="/tmp/shell.so"` can inject arbitrary executables.

**Proof of Concept:**
```json
{
  "environment": {
    "PATH": "/tmp:$PATH",
    "LD_PRELOAD": "/tmp/backdoor.so"
  }
}
```

**Fix:**
```typescript
export function parseEnvironment(value: unknown): Record<string, string> | undefined {
  const ALLOWED_ENV_KEYS = new Set([
    "NODE_OPTIONS", "PYTHONPATH", "JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS", "RUST_BACKTRACE"
  ]);
  const environment: Record<string, string> = {};

  for (const [rawKey, rawValue] of Object.entries(value as Record<string, unknown>)) {
    const key = rawKey.trim();
    if (!ALLOWED_ENV_KEYS.has(key)) continue;  // Whitelist, not blacklist
    if (typeof rawValue !== "string" || rawValue.length > 4096) continue;  // Bound length
    environment[key] = rawValue;
  }
  return environment;
}
```

