|----------|------|-----|
| **NOW** | `src/agents/manager.ts` | Validate resolved path stays in base dir |
| **NOW** | `src/settings/settings-parsers.ts` | Whitelist allowed env vars; bound length |
| **SOON** | `src/state/db.ts` | Add Zod schemas before JSON.parse |
| **SOON** | `src/execution/runner.ts` | Sanitize env passed to spawn; bound artifact paths |
| **NICE** | `src/teams/validator.ts` | Tighten NAME_PATTERN regex |

---

**Recommendation:** Implement a **trust boundary** audit: identify which inputs come from config files (trusted), CLI (semi-trusted), or API (untrusted), then apply validation at each boundary. The agent name and environment variables are the highest-risk attack surface here.
